SYNOPSIS (OPTIONAL)
===================
   void sl_close()

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Closes the SQLite database associated with the current object.

   The function is available only if the driver is compiled with SQLite 
   support. In that case, __SQLITE__ is defined.

HISTORY
=======
   - introduced (3.3.713)

SEE ALSO
========
   sl_open(E), sl_exec(E), sl_insert_id(E)
